WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:00:42.630 --> 00:00:46.170
<i>Today the United States Senate Committee
on Government Operations</i>

3
00:00:46.250 --> 00:00:48.790
<i>begins hearings
on federally insured banks.</i>

4
00:00:50.000 --> 00:00:53.710
<i>We are concerned whether existing laws
are adequate to guarantee</i>

5
00:00:53.790 --> 00:00:58.250
<i>the character. experience. and integrity
of people who acquire such banks.</i>

6
00:00:59.380 --> 00:01:02.210
<i>which are the cornerstones
of American capitalism</i>

7
00:01:03.000 --> 00:01:05.000
<i>and the foundation of the American dream.</i>

8
00:01:31.460 --> 00:01:35.460
<i>Be careful in there. Bernard.
They want to make an example out of you.</i>

9
00:01:50.340 --> 00:01:53.000
Committee calls Bernard S. Garrett
to testify.

10
00:01:55.540 --> 00:01:58.290
Mr. Garrett.
I think you understand the stakes.

11
00:02:07.170 --> 00:02:08.460
Carlyle and Spring?

12
00:02:08.540 --> 00:02:11.840
Right. Annual rental income 80.000.
which is strong.

13
00:02:11.920 --> 00:02:14.590
but Mr. Miller wants us
to use a six multiplier to value it.

14
00:02:14.670 --> 00:02:16.050
That's too high.

15
00:02:16.130 --> 00:02:19.340
He's coming in an hour to negotiate on it.
Maybe you can step in.

16
00:02:19.420 --> 00:02:20.420
All right.

17
00:02:24.290 --> 00:02:25.920
Boy does a pretty good shine.

18
00:02:26.500 --> 00:02:27.880
Harder worker than most of 'em.

19
00:02:41.340 --> 00:02:42.660
There may not be comps in Willis.

20
00:02:42.710 --> 00:02:45.290
but take a look at
the other properties I own in the county.

21
00:02:45.380 --> 00:02:46.880
A six multiple is reasonable.

22
00:02:47.800 --> 00:02:51.500
Your other buildings are in Conroe.
which is booming with the oil find.

23
00:02:51.590 --> 00:02:54.170
So. I'm not sure this is a good comp.

24
00:02:54.840 --> 00:02:55.840
Willis is booming too.

25
00:02:55.920 --> 00:02:57.750
Hey! What are you doing up there. boy?

26
00:02:57.840 --> 00:02:59.960
You spying on these
white people's business?

27
00:03:06.630 --> 00:03:07.630
Get back here!

28
00:03:09.960 --> 00:03:11.460
Your dad's gonna hear about this!

29
00:03:11.540 --> 00:03:12.540
Hey! Watch it. boy!

30
00:03:32.840 --> 00:03:36.420
What do you think them white folks would
do if they knew you were spying on them?

31
00:03:38.290 --> 00:03:40.590
When I was growing up
I've seen boys killed for less.

32
00:03:43.380 --> 00:03:46.380
You know what it's like to see a young boy
hanging dead from a tree?

33
00:03:47.750 --> 00:03:51.130
And don't think because it hasn't happened
recently. it couldn't happen again.

34
00:03:51.210 --> 00:03:53.250
I was just trying to learn
how they make money.

35
00:03:58.130 --> 00:04:00.420
You are so talented.

36
00:04:01.340 --> 00:04:02.920
How did you learn all this?

37
00:04:07.500 --> 00:04:09.250
You was born the wrong color. son.

38
00:04:09.340 --> 00:04:11.170
Negro man can't earn money with this.

39
00:04:11.250 --> 00:04:13.750
White man won't let him.
no matter how good at it you are.

40
00:04:15.670 --> 00:04:17.050
Maybe not in Texas.

41
00:04:19.630 --> 00:04:22.840
You really think it's gonna be different
for you. you go somewhere else?

42
00:05:03.540 --> 00:05:05.460
We're in California.

43
00:05:08.340 --> 00:05:09.340
What's wrong?

44
00:05:10.840 --> 00:05:13.590
Just looking forward
to having dinner with your uncle.

45
00:05:17.210 --> 00:05:20.170
Well. the aircraft companies are booming.

46
00:05:20.710 --> 00:05:24.590
Northrop is looking to hire 5.000
new workers for their assembly line

47
00:05:24.670 --> 00:05:26.420
and they hire our kind.

48
00:05:26.500 --> 00:05:28.670
And I can get you
an interview there tomorrow.

49
00:05:28.750 --> 00:05:31.880
Well. thank you. sir. But I came here
to try my hand at real estate.

50
00:05:32.420 --> 00:05:34.880
There's not a lot
of colored real estate agents.

51
00:05:34.960 --> 00:05:36.500
Owning property and renting it out.

52
00:05:38.840 --> 00:05:40.340
You married a millionaire. Eunice?

53
00:05:41.590 --> 00:05:42.590
Deacon.

54
00:05:45.170 --> 00:05:46.880
Well. I sure hope you're close. son.

55
00:05:47.340 --> 00:05:49.250
This isn't some one-horse town in Texas.

56
00:05:49.340 --> 00:05:50.960
Real estate is expensive here.

57
00:05:51.670 --> 00:05:54.960
Bernard saved up money
from a company we started in Houston.

58
00:05:56.250 --> 00:05:59.710
So. what do you plan to do
until you find something you can afford?

59
00:05:59.800 --> 00:06:00.880
Keep looking.

60
00:06:00.960 --> 00:06:03.090
And spend down your savings
till they're gone?

61
00:06:03.670 --> 00:06:05.000
And then can't pay your rent?

62
00:06:05.090 --> 00:06:06.460
Deacon. stop.

63
00:06:07.710 --> 00:06:09.800
You'll get your rent
the first of every month.

64
00:06:09.880 --> 00:06:11.340
one month in advance.

65
00:06:11.960 --> 00:06:13.750
I should go get Bernard Jr. in bed.

66
00:06:14.710 --> 00:06:15.710
Excuse me.

67
00:06:28.670 --> 00:06:30.960
<i>Eunice. what does your husband have
against working?</i>

68
00:06:31.420 --> 00:06:34.960
If we need to supplement our income
until he finds the right property.

69
00:06:35.040 --> 00:06:36.670
I'll work at the Plantation Club.

70
00:06:36.750 --> 00:06:39.000
That ain't no place
for a married woman to work.

71
00:06:39.090 --> 00:06:40.600
Bernard okay with you going back there?

72
00:06:40.630 --> 00:06:42.500
Well. we haven't had a chance
to discuss it.

73
00:06:43.380 --> 00:06:45.040
If he's a real man. he won't let you.

74
00:06:45.130 --> 00:06:46.920
That won't be for him to decide.

75
00:06:47.590 --> 00:06:48.710
What does that mean?

76
00:06:50.130 --> 00:06:52.170
My husband is a genius.

77
00:06:52.250 --> 00:06:53.250
You'll see.

78
00:07:04.130 --> 00:07:05.710
I know this isn't much.

79
00:07:05.800 --> 00:07:07.630
Yeah. I don't plan on us being here long.

80
00:07:08.630 --> 00:07:10.170
Why are you so hard on yourself?

81
00:07:10.250 --> 00:07:12.750
I don't want Bernard Jr.
Growing up in a shed.

82
00:07:14.170 --> 00:07:16.710
Well. I grew up in a shed.

83
00:07:17.550 --> 00:07:19.750
Abraham Lincoln grew up in a shed.

84
00:07:19.840 --> 00:07:21.880
Abraham Lincoln grew up in a log cabin.

85
00:07:21.960 --> 00:07:25.250
Well. that's what they call a shed
when it's in the woods.

86
00:07:25.340 --> 00:07:26.960
There's no difference.

87
00:07:27.040 --> 00:07:29.630
Well. I'm gonna get you and him
out of this shed.

88
00:07:31.420 --> 00:07:32.590
As soon as possible.

89
00:07:38.670 --> 00:07:39.670
Thanks for the lift.

90
00:07:39.750 --> 00:07:41.000
No problem.

91
00:07:41.090 --> 00:07:42.960
I'm sorry my dad was such a jerk
last night.

92
00:07:43.380 --> 00:07:45.550
Was he? I didn't notice.

93
00:07:47.670 --> 00:07:49.050
Hey. nice car.

94
00:07:49.130 --> 00:07:49.960
Thanks.

95
00:07:50.040 --> 00:07:51.590
Bernard. this is my friend Matt.

96
00:07:51.670 --> 00:07:53.950
You didn't tell me you had a rich uncle.
Nice to meet you.

97
00:07:54.000 --> 00:07:55.420
Hardly rich. And I'm his cousin.

98
00:07:56.040 --> 00:07:57.670
You got a car. you're rich to me.

99
00:07:58.960 --> 00:08:00.750
Hey. good luck finding the right place.

100
00:08:04.550 --> 00:08:05.630
Hey.

101
00:08:08.170 --> 00:08:09.920
Hey. what's your cousin do for a living?

102
00:08:10.550 --> 00:08:11.630
He owns buildings.

103
00:08:12.380 --> 00:08:13.420
Really?

104
00:08:13.790 --> 00:08:14.790
Damn.

105
00:08:23.550 --> 00:08:25.090
<i>Hello. my name is Bernard Garrett.</i>

106
00:08:25.170 --> 00:08:28.630
<i>I saw your property on Victoria Road.
I was wondering what the asking price...</i>

107
00:08:28.710 --> 00:08:31.340
<i>Hello. my name is Bernard Garrett.
Are you the owner of 12...</i>

108
00:08:31.420 --> 00:08:34.000
<i>Hi. my name is Bernard Garrett.
I'm a real estate investor.</i>

109
00:08:34.090 --> 00:08:35.170
<i>What's the asking price?</i>

110
00:08:35.250 --> 00:08:36.250
<i>That high?</i>

111
00:08:36.290 --> 00:08:39.210
<i>How can a price that high be sustainable.
given the current rents...</i>

112
00:08:39.290 --> 00:08:41.480
<i>How many units are in the building
and what are they really...</i>

113
00:08:41.500 --> 00:08:43.150
<i>Looks to me
the building needs a little work.</i>

114
00:08:43.170 --> 00:08:44.340
<i>Maybe we can negotiate...</i>

115
00:08:44.420 --> 00:08:46.840
<i>Right. I understand.
Thank you for your time.</i>

116
00:08:50.170 --> 00:08:52.090
This is a white neighborhood. Bernard.

117
00:08:52.170 --> 00:08:53.790
Well. it won't be white for long.

118
00:08:53.880 --> 00:08:57.290
Not with the black neighborhood
two blocks away bursting at the seams.

119
00:08:58.710 --> 00:09:00.960
Well. how much
does Barker & Associates want for it?

120
00:09:01.960 --> 00:09:03.540
We have enough to buy it.

121
00:09:03.630 --> 00:09:05.920
Just won't have anything left over
to fix it up with.

122
00:09:07.210 --> 00:09:09.130
What if I got us a co-investor?

123
00:09:32.880 --> 00:09:35.540
All right. fellows. That was smokin'.

124
00:09:35.630 --> 00:09:36.750
Joe!

125
00:09:38.000 --> 00:09:39.460
Eunice!

126
00:09:39.550 --> 00:09:41.960
You came back to me.

127
00:09:43.750 --> 00:09:45.420
Girl. look at you.

128
00:09:45.500 --> 00:09:47.290
Stop it. Behave now.

129
00:09:47.380 --> 00:09:48.420
Honey.

130
00:09:50.170 --> 00:09:51.290
Who's this?

131
00:09:51.380 --> 00:09:53.800
That uncle
you was always talking to me about?

132
00:09:54.460 --> 00:09:55.460
Husband.

133
00:09:55.670 --> 00:09:56.840
Your hus... What?

134
00:09:56.920 --> 00:09:58.000
Wait.

135
00:09:58.090 --> 00:09:59.460
Three years.

136
00:10:00.550 --> 00:10:01.920
Congratulations. man.

137
00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:03.130
You hit the jackpot.

138
00:10:03.210 --> 00:10:04.710
If you're the marrying type.

139
00:10:04.790 --> 00:10:09.670
I'm not. but if I were.
can't do no better than Eunice Perkins.

140
00:10:09.750 --> 00:10:10.790
Garrett.

141
00:10:10.880 --> 00:10:12.380
Pleased to meet you. Garrett.

142
00:10:12.460 --> 00:10:13.590
No. I'm Bernard.

143
00:10:14.040 --> 00:10:16.060
I heard him say "Garrett."
Didn't you hear him say "Garrett"?

144
00:10:16.090 --> 00:10:17.090
That's what I heard.

145
00:10:19.040 --> 00:10:20.710
I'm just messing with you. man.

146
00:10:20.790 --> 00:10:21.790
You want a drink?

147
00:10:21.880 --> 00:10:22.880
It's 4:00 p.m.

148
00:10:22.960 --> 00:10:24.590
I know. You're starting late.

149
00:10:24.670 --> 00:10:26.130
I'll have 'em make it strong.

150
00:10:26.210 --> 00:10:28.880
Jackie. make my man here something strong.

151
00:10:28.960 --> 00:10:29.960
A triple.

152
00:10:30.040 --> 00:10:32.300
You know. see if we can blow
the stick out of his ass.

153
00:10:33.460 --> 00:10:36.210
You did not even talk to him
about your idea.

154
00:10:36.300 --> 00:10:38.210
No way am I doing business with that man.

155
00:10:38.300 --> 00:10:40.750
Not for a loan.
Especially not as a business partner.

156
00:10:40.840 --> 00:10:41.840
He's a damn degenerate.

157
00:10:41.920 --> 00:10:43.750
Bernard. please!

158
00:10:45.500 --> 00:10:46.880
I don't need his help.

159
00:10:49.300 --> 00:10:52.300
You have got the wrong idea about him.

160
00:10:52.380 --> 00:10:54.210
Really? You think so?

161
00:10:55.040 --> 00:10:57.170
'Cause the vice squad
seems to disagree with you.

162
00:10:58.210 --> 00:11:00.000
Well. that's the mayor. silly.

163
00:11:00.090 --> 00:11:02.420
Do you wanna meet him?
Because he's friends with Joe.

164
00:11:04.250 --> 00:11:05.340
No.

165
00:11:06.550 --> 00:11:08.210
If you won't let Joe invest.

166
00:11:08.300 --> 00:11:10.960
then you are gonna have to
make Barker come down on his price.

167
00:11:18.380 --> 00:11:20.250
Asking price is 40.000.

168
00:11:20.670 --> 00:11:22.290
You won't get a penny over 35.

169
00:11:22.380 --> 00:11:23.670
You offering 35?

170
00:11:23.750 --> 00:11:25.130
I can give you 30.

171
00:11:25.630 --> 00:11:28.130
Why would I take 30 if I can get 35?

172
00:11:28.210 --> 00:11:31.000
Well. the building needs renovations
to unlock its value.

173
00:11:31.090 --> 00:11:32.460
It's been fine for my tenants.

174
00:11:32.550 --> 00:11:34.500
Your tenants only occupy
half the building.

175
00:11:34.880 --> 00:11:37.340
But with new kitchens
and refinished floors...

176
00:11:37.420 --> 00:11:41.210
My tenants won't pay more even if they
can see the reflections in those floors.

177
00:11:41.300 --> 00:11:42.710
But another market will.

178
00:11:43.670 --> 00:11:46.380
Black doctors. lawyers. teachers

179
00:11:46.460 --> 00:11:49.840
looking for a place to move outside
the ghettos that they've been forced into.

180
00:11:50.340 --> 00:11:52.130
No one is going after that market.

181
00:11:52.210 --> 00:11:53.210
But I can.

182
00:11:55.630 --> 00:11:57.460
Your confidence is impressive.

183
00:11:57.540 --> 00:12:01.250
But 10.000 less than asking is not enough.

184
00:12:01.340 --> 00:12:04.210
Once I lease the units.
I can give you your full asking price.

185
00:12:04.300 --> 00:12:05.290
Let's say by...

186
00:12:06.500 --> 00:12:07.710
June.

187
00:12:07.790 --> 00:12:12.210
You want me to loan you $10.000
so you can buy my building?

188
00:12:12.300 --> 00:12:13.880
It's not a loan. It's an investment.

189
00:12:13.960 --> 00:12:15.090
It's a loan.

190
00:12:15.670 --> 00:12:19.210
For more than three times what the average
American family make in a year.

191
00:12:19.300 --> 00:12:21.500
- Two point four times.
- What?

192
00:12:21.590 --> 00:12:26.170
The average American income in 1953
was $4.233.

193
00:12:26.250 --> 00:12:29.500
Ten thousand is 2.4 times
the average income.

194
00:12:31.460 --> 00:12:35.500
Well. I admire your entrepreneurial gusto.

195
00:12:35.590 --> 00:12:38.500
but it's not the way I do business.

196
00:12:39.920 --> 00:12:40.920
I'm sorry.

197
00:12:48.960 --> 00:12:50.630
Thank you for your time. Mr. Barker.

198
00:13:08.670 --> 00:13:10.460
Look what just walked in.

199
00:13:10.540 --> 00:13:11.960
Mighty fancy for a colored fella.

200
00:13:12.880 --> 00:13:13.880
We'll see.

201
00:13:14.540 --> 00:13:17.500
Hi. I'm Bernard Garrett.
I'd like to speak with Mr. Reed. please.

202
00:13:17.590 --> 00:13:20.250
I'm sorry. Mr. Reed is out.
May I take a message?

203
00:13:21.960 --> 00:13:25.880
I have pretty good eyesight and I can
clearly read the nameplate on his desk.

204
00:13:27.340 --> 00:13:29.090
I'm sorry. I misspoke.

205
00:13:30.130 --> 00:13:31.880
Mr. Reed can't meet with you right now.

206
00:13:31.960 --> 00:13:33.210
But I could take a message.

207
00:13:35.090 --> 00:13:37.460
No. There's no message.

208
00:13:38.340 --> 00:13:39.340
Thank you.

209
00:13:48.500 --> 00:13:49.790
Mr. Reed.

210
00:13:49.880 --> 00:13:50.880
Do I know you?

211
00:13:50.960 --> 00:13:52.340
No. But you know Mr. Barker.

212
00:13:52.420 --> 00:13:54.290
I'd like a loan
to buy one of his buildings.

213
00:13:54.380 --> 00:13:56.550
Yeah. you can make
an appointment inside. please.

214
00:13:56.630 --> 00:13:59.670
Well. you and I both know
I'm not getting an appointment inside.

215
00:14:00.670 --> 00:14:03.500
Now. this deal will benefit Mr. Barker.

216
00:14:04.460 --> 00:14:05.460
You should hear me out.

217
00:14:08.130 --> 00:14:10.550
Your uncle gonna get a good laugh
out of this one.

218
00:14:13.250 --> 00:14:15.880
Keep looking. You're gonna find yourself
another building.

219
00:14:17.040 --> 00:14:18.040
Yeah.

220
00:14:20.710 --> 00:14:22.340
Come on. Time for bed. little man.

221
00:14:23.170 --> 00:14:24.000
Yes?

222
00:14:24.090 --> 00:14:26.880
Bernard. there's a phone call for you.

223
00:14:31.880 --> 00:14:35.050
- Hello?
<i>- Mr. Garrett. This is Patrick Barker.</i>

224
00:14:35.670 --> 00:14:40.590
Did you use my name to try and get a loan
from Mr. Reed at Mid City Bank?

225
00:14:41.170 --> 00:14:42.840
Well. in a manner of speaking...

226
00:14:43.670 --> 00:14:44.670
yes.

227
00:14:45.380 --> 00:14:48.460
And do you think that follows
normal business customs?

228
00:14:49.790 --> 00:14:51.630
If I was following
normal business customs.

229
00:14:51.710 --> 00:14:53.750
I'd still be a shoeshine boy
in Texas. sir.

230
00:14:53.840 --> 00:14:56.420
I didn't ask for your biography.
Mr. Garrett.

231
00:14:56.500 --> 00:15:00.130
I asked if you thought
it followed normal business customs.

232
00:15:02.460 --> 00:15:03.880
- No.
<i>- Good.</i>

233
00:15:03.960 --> 00:15:05.630
Well. at least we can agree on that.

234
00:15:07.670 --> 00:15:11.460
Reed wants to see you at the bank
in the morning to sign off on that loan.

235
00:15:12.050 --> 00:15:13.090
Excuse me?

236
00:15:13.540 --> 00:15:15.670
<i>I told him I'd act as guarantor.</i>

237
00:15:18.210 --> 00:15:19.250
You still there?

238
00:15:21.500 --> 00:15:23.090
Why are you doing this. Mr. Barker?

239
00:15:23.170 --> 00:15:24.920
Because normal business customs

240
00:15:25.000 --> 00:15:27.670
are in place to screw people like you.
Mr. Garrett.

241
00:15:28.130 --> 00:15:31.130
<i>You went to see Reed
knowing the deck was stacked</i>

242
00:15:31.210 --> 00:15:34.000
<i>because you have
that much confidence in this deal.</i>

243
00:15:35.000 --> 00:15:36.920
That tells me
all I need to know about you.

244
00:15:40.130 --> 00:15:41.750
Well. do you want this loan or not?

245
00:15:44.840 --> 00:15:46.130
Yes.

246
00:15:50.840 --> 00:15:55.460
Sometimes you need to take a step back
and enjoy what you've accomplished. baby.

247
00:16:28.670 --> 00:16:29.750
You like cigars?

248
00:16:31.380 --> 00:16:32.460
I don't smoke.

249
00:16:41.920 --> 00:16:43.840
I'm not fucking your wife.

250
00:16:45.590 --> 00:16:48.670
You go to every table in here
to reassure your patrons of that?

251
00:16:48.750 --> 00:16:51.380
No. Might have to skip some of them.

252
00:16:53.750 --> 00:16:55.090
Come on. man. Lighten up.

253
00:16:55.170 --> 00:16:56.960
I'm not the asshole you think I am.

254
00:16:57.050 --> 00:16:59.130
You a different kind of asshole. huh?

255
00:17:02.290 --> 00:17:03.880
I've been told that. yeah.

256
00:17:04.630 --> 00:17:06.250
Come on. Let's go outside and talk.

257
00:17:19.420 --> 00:17:20.840
What do you want from me. man?

258
00:17:21.420 --> 00:17:23.340
You mean aside from your wife?

259
00:17:26.460 --> 00:17:30.250
Look. I like seeing black men succeed.

260
00:17:30.340 --> 00:17:33.340
Sometimes I even invest
some of my own money to back them.

261
00:17:34.710 --> 00:17:36.050
But you don't even know me.

262
00:17:36.130 --> 00:17:38.130
I know you're smart and ambitious.

263
00:17:39.500 --> 00:17:41.340
You and I both know that's not enough.

264
00:17:41.420 --> 00:17:42.920
You're also angry.

265
00:17:43.790 --> 00:17:44.920
But you don't show it.

266
00:17:45.500 --> 00:17:47.250
That's the best kind of anger.

267
00:17:47.340 --> 00:17:49.420
Fuels you without making you a target.

268
00:17:50.590 --> 00:17:51.590
I'm not angry.

269
00:17:54.710 --> 00:17:55.750
Yeah. all right.

270
00:18:00.590 --> 00:18:01.630
Nice glasses.

271
00:18:01.710 --> 00:18:03.130
You near-sighted or far-sighted?

272
00:18:03.790 --> 00:18:04.790
Does it matter?

273
00:18:05.710 --> 00:18:07.790
Just wondering what you'd look like
without 'em.

274
00:18:13.500 --> 00:18:15.090
So. you trust this Barker?

275
00:18:16.170 --> 00:18:17.420
He didn't have to help me.

276
00:18:18.500 --> 00:18:21.880
What if you can't finish the work
or rent the units fast enough?

277
00:18:22.750 --> 00:18:23.790
I'll make the date.

278
00:18:25.790 --> 00:18:28.460
See? Anger.

279
00:18:30.170 --> 00:18:31.540
I'm gonna get another drink.

280
00:18:36.540 --> 00:18:37.590
I'm not angry.

281
00:18:38.880 --> 00:18:39.960
Yes. you are.

282
00:18:49.840 --> 00:18:51.380
What are you doing here?

283
00:18:51.840 --> 00:18:55.380
Ma'am. I'm Bernard Garrett.

284
00:18:55.460 --> 00:18:57.710
Just doing some renovations
on the empty apartments.

285
00:18:58.130 --> 00:18:59.880
What hours do you work?

286
00:18:59.960 --> 00:19:03.880
Well. the city say all construction has to
be done between 8:00 a.m. and 6:00 p.m.

287
00:19:03.960 --> 00:19:07.300
- So. if you need any improvements...
- I don't need improvements.

288
00:19:07.710 --> 00:19:10.460
And you can tell
that mick that owns this place.

289
00:19:10.540 --> 00:19:14.000
when he goes jacking the rent.
he ain't jacking mine.

290
00:19:14.090 --> 00:19:15.090
Yes. ma'am.

291
00:19:15.130 --> 00:19:18.340
Mr. Barker was very clear about your lease
when he sold me the building.

292
00:19:19.420 --> 00:19:21.590
Don't you sass me. boy.

293
00:19:21.960 --> 00:19:23.460
This is a white building.

294
00:19:24.290 --> 00:19:26.210
You can't own this place.

295
00:19:36.630 --> 00:19:39.380
Hey. why don't you grab that scraper
and start on the other end?

296
00:19:39.920 --> 00:19:40.960
All right.

297
00:19:42.800 --> 00:19:43.840
- Hey. man.
- Hey.

298
00:19:44.670 --> 00:19:45.750
Hey. thanks for coming.

299
00:19:45.840 --> 00:19:46.840
Of course.

300
00:19:48.340 --> 00:19:49.420
How's it going?

301
00:19:50.050 --> 00:19:51.630
I can offer you a buck. 50 an hour.

302
00:19:51.710 --> 00:19:52.960
That's great.

303
00:19:53.050 --> 00:19:54.750
And you're fine with working for me?

304
00:19:54.840 --> 00:19:56.670
I've been working for other men
my whole life.

305
00:19:56.750 --> 00:19:59.290
Right. But are you okay
with working for me?

306
00:20:00.420 --> 00:20:03.380
Well. your money is green.
That's the only concern about color I got.

307
00:20:03.800 --> 00:20:06.090
And I like the idea
of watching you build a business.

308
00:20:06.170 --> 00:20:08.290
It's something I'd like to do again
myself one day.

309
00:20:08.380 --> 00:20:09.420
"Again"?

310
00:20:09.500 --> 00:20:11.420
Yeah. I tried something a few years back.

311
00:20:11.500 --> 00:20:13.710
It was a drive-in ice cream shop.

312
00:20:14.500 --> 00:20:17.880
Well. it turns out people don't wanna
eat ice cream while driving their cars.

313
00:20:21.000 --> 00:20:22.800
- You serious?
- Yeah.

314
00:20:27.420 --> 00:20:28.800
- Let's get to work.
- Yeah.

315
00:20:32.130 --> 00:20:34.170
Connect it here. Like this.

316
00:20:36.670 --> 00:20:37.670
Should be good.

317
00:20:46.340 --> 00:20:47.340
Step back.

318
00:20:51.670 --> 00:20:52.670
Right there.

319
00:20:53.340 --> 00:20:55.420
We want to scrape these railings
up to the front

320
00:20:55.500 --> 00:20:58.090
and paint our way back
and then go back with the stucco.

321
00:20:58.170 --> 00:21:00.500
Go from the top. Let's work our way down.

322
00:21:00.590 --> 00:21:02.000
- Bernard Garrett.
- Then let's...

323
00:21:03.540 --> 00:21:05.340
Yes. Officer. Is there a problem?

324
00:21:05.420 --> 00:21:07.090
We received a complaint about you.

325
00:21:07.590 --> 00:21:10.670
Ms. Cooper in Apartment 2A
does not like you working in the building.

326
00:21:11.960 --> 00:21:12.800
Why not?

327
00:21:12.880 --> 00:21:14.730
She said you were impersonating
the owner of the building.

328
00:21:14.750 --> 00:21:17.380
- No. he owns the building.
- I'm not talking to you.

329
00:21:20.420 --> 00:21:22.090
I do own the building. Officer.

330
00:21:22.170 --> 00:21:24.630
All the paperwork is filed downtown.

331
00:21:24.710 --> 00:21:27.670
But I keep a copy with me.
just to be safe.

332
00:21:33.840 --> 00:21:35.000
This actually looks real.

333
00:21:41.920 --> 00:21:43.050
Yeah. I guess so.

334
00:21:45.540 --> 00:21:47.460
Try to be more respectful to your tenants.

335
00:21:48.920 --> 00:21:50.130
Yes. sir. Officer.

336
00:21:51.250 --> 00:21:52.880
Sorry for the inconvenience.

337
00:22:02.670 --> 00:22:06.050
You can't be here after 6:00 p.m.

338
00:22:06.130 --> 00:22:09.090
A contractor can't be here
after 6:00 p.m.. Ms. Cooper.

339
00:22:09.630 --> 00:22:11.000
I'm a resident.

340
00:22:11.090 --> 00:22:12.090
I'm moving in.

341
00:22:28.040 --> 00:22:30.090
I hope your mother enjoys her new place.

342
00:22:30.170 --> 00:22:31.460
I'm sure she will.

343
00:22:31.540 --> 00:22:33.040
- Mrs. Garrett?
- Yes.

344
00:22:33.130 --> 00:22:36.170
Anita Jefferson. We spoke about
leasing one of your apartments?

345
00:22:36.250 --> 00:22:38.170
Yes. of course. It's nice to meet you.

346
00:22:41.000 --> 00:22:42.210
Fully leased.

347
00:22:43.290 --> 00:22:44.340
Impressive.

348
00:22:47.920 --> 00:22:50.840
I have my eye on a place
two blocks east of here.

349
00:22:51.420 --> 00:22:52.500
You interested?

350
00:22:52.590 --> 00:22:53.590
You mean a partnership?

351
00:22:54.500 --> 00:22:55.630
Yeah. 50-50.

352
00:22:56.550 --> 00:22:57.630
But on one condition.

353
00:22:59.880 --> 00:23:00.880
Bernard...

354
00:23:01.500 --> 00:23:02.750
I do business with people

355
00:23:03.420 --> 00:23:05.460
who turn away from me
after we shake on the deal

356
00:23:05.550 --> 00:23:07.960
and wash their hands
because I'm a dirty Irishman.

357
00:23:09.550 --> 00:23:12.290
But they do business with me
because I make them money.

358
00:23:13.630 --> 00:23:17.250
Now. you have the knack of knowing
the untapped value of a building.

359
00:23:18.960 --> 00:23:20.880
You'll work the phones with me.

360
00:23:22.340 --> 00:23:23.420
Work the investors.

361
00:23:24.250 --> 00:23:28.090
But when we need a face to sign the deal.
that'll be me.

362
00:23:29.750 --> 00:23:30.750
And we'll make money.

363
00:23:31.840 --> 00:23:32.840
A lot of it.

364
00:23:35.290 --> 00:23:36.290
Fifty-fifty?

365
00:23:39.000 --> 00:23:40.210
Fifty-fifty.

366
00:23:47.250 --> 00:23:48.250
This is it. Right here.

367
00:23:48.670 --> 00:23:49.670
There you go.

368
00:23:52.000 --> 00:23:53.000
Your signature.

369
00:24:02.630 --> 00:24:03.880
Hello? Yeah.

370
00:24:04.500 --> 00:24:05.500
Right.

371
00:24:07.380 --> 00:24:08.800
I was calling about the house...

372
00:24:34.250 --> 00:24:35.630
Let's try the sofa over here.

373
00:24:36.210 --> 00:24:38.590
Lamp. Right here in the corner.

374
00:24:38.670 --> 00:24:40.750
It's perfect. Perfect. Perfect.

375
00:24:41.250 --> 00:24:43.170
That looks great.

376
00:24:43.710 --> 00:24:45.630
What do you think. baby? It's nice. right?

377
00:24:45.710 --> 00:24:48.210
Well. I think there's something going on
with the car.

378
00:24:48.290 --> 00:24:49.460
You wanna go check on it?

379
00:24:51.250 --> 00:24:52.250
Right.

380
00:24:54.000 --> 00:24:56.500
Okay. let's move the table there.
slide the couch in.

381
00:24:56.590 --> 00:24:58.210
and put the lamp on the other side.

382
00:24:58.960 --> 00:25:01.880
And don't you dare let him move anything
when he gets back. Okay?

383
00:25:01.960 --> 00:25:03.210
- Yes. ma'am.
- Yes. ma'am.

384
00:25:05.920 --> 00:25:09.500
Barker and I have been thinking about
diversifying in single family homes.

385
00:25:10.630 --> 00:25:11.630
So...

386
00:25:12.550 --> 00:25:16.880
want you to go in. tell me
what you think this house needs.

387
00:25:24.710 --> 00:25:25.800
Bernard.

388
00:25:28.290 --> 00:25:29.920
This place is beautiful.

389
00:25:31.670 --> 00:25:32.670
You think?

390
00:25:33.170 --> 00:25:34.920
- Yes.
- Does it need anything?

391
00:25:35.000 --> 00:25:36.170
Furniture.

392
00:25:37.340 --> 00:25:38.920
So I did a good job?

393
00:25:39.000 --> 00:25:40.840
Well. it depends on the price. doesn't it?

394
00:25:42.550 --> 00:25:43.670
Not this time. baby.

395
00:25:46.550 --> 00:25:48.290
Go on. Take it. I already got a set.

396
00:25:50.420 --> 00:25:52.210
Are you serious?

397
00:25:57.550 --> 00:25:59.340
You really sleeping in late.

398
00:25:59.920 --> 00:26:01.670
Time to get up. dear.

399
00:26:16.000 --> 00:26:18.040
<i>Mrs. Barker would like to offer a buyout</i>

400
00:26:18.130 --> 00:26:21.550
for your interest
in all the Barker/Garrett properties.

401
00:26:21.630 --> 00:26:23.290
I have no reason to sell.

402
00:26:23.380 --> 00:26:25.210
I'm happy running the buildings on my own.

403
00:26:25.290 --> 00:26:26.670
That's unacceptable.

404
00:26:26.750 --> 00:26:28.190
I don't wanna be in business with...

405
00:26:29.880 --> 00:26:33.000
I prefer not to continue the arrangement.

406
00:26:34.880 --> 00:26:36.130
What's the offer?

407
00:26:45.090 --> 00:26:46.670
This is outrageous.

408
00:26:46.750 --> 00:26:49.790
I own 50% of a dozen properties.

409
00:26:49.880 --> 00:26:52.340
You want me to give it up
for pennies on the dollar?

410
00:26:52.420 --> 00:26:54.800
I don't have to pay you anything.

411
00:26:55.460 --> 00:26:57.420
Your name doesn't appear
on any of the deeds.

412
00:26:57.500 --> 00:26:58.630
Well. it couldn't.

413
00:26:59.130 --> 00:27:00.250
We had an agreement.

414
00:27:00.340 --> 00:27:02.960
And we all know
what your husband's intentions were.

415
00:27:07.340 --> 00:27:10.380
I will up my offer
to 25 cents on the dollar.

416
00:27:10.460 --> 00:27:12.630
And if you see fit
to refuse that. Mr. Garrett.

417
00:27:12.710 --> 00:27:14.340
you can walk away with nothing

418
00:27:14.880 --> 00:27:16.790
unless you wanna face me
in a court of law.

419
00:27:17.590 --> 00:27:18.880
With a different lawyer.

420
00:27:25.380 --> 00:27:27.750
There has to be a way
to prove Mr. Barker's intentions.

421
00:27:27.840 --> 00:27:29.960
Well. if you could find a witness. yes.

422
00:27:30.040 --> 00:27:31.040
But...

423
00:27:31.420 --> 00:27:32.420
it can't be me.

424
00:27:33.000 --> 00:27:34.420
I could get disbarred for that.

425
00:27:35.300 --> 00:27:37.420
Mr. Reed at Mid City...

426
00:27:37.500 --> 00:27:39.630
He's her banker now. Bernard.

427
00:27:41.000 --> 00:27:42.670
He's not going to intervene for you.

428
00:27:47.500 --> 00:27:48.960
I need to see Mr. Reed.

429
00:27:49.040 --> 00:27:50.460
I'm sorry. Mr. Garrett.

430
00:27:50.550 --> 00:27:52.920
Mr. Reed can't see anybody
without an appointment.

431
00:27:53.000 --> 00:27:54.000
This is urgent.

432
00:27:56.420 --> 00:27:57.460
Hold on a moment.

433
00:29:01.090 --> 00:29:04.300
I don't know how familiar you are
with the commercial real estate market.

434
00:29:04.380 --> 00:29:07.170
Eunice told me you had two or three
income-producing buildings?

435
00:29:08.090 --> 00:29:09.300
Seventeen.

436
00:29:09.380 --> 00:29:11.630
But once you've popped your cherry.

437
00:29:11.710 --> 00:29:14.210
I mean. how much more
can you learn on each new one?

438
00:29:15.790 --> 00:29:16.840
Seventeen?

439
00:29:17.710 --> 00:29:19.130
Eighteen. if you count the club.

440
00:29:19.920 --> 00:29:21.590
My mother was a real estate agent.

441
00:29:22.880 --> 00:29:23.960
You know this building?

442
00:29:26.920 --> 00:29:29.790
Sure. Bunch of bankers headquarters
in there.

443
00:29:29.880 --> 00:29:32.790
Tallest commercial building
in downtown Los Angeles.

444
00:29:32.880 --> 00:29:33.920
I wanna buy it.

445
00:29:36.090 --> 00:29:37.130
I want us to buy it.

446
00:29:40.960 --> 00:29:45.250
That's a mighty big building to buy
on the most expensive land in the city.

447
00:29:45.340 --> 00:29:46.340
I know.

448
00:29:48.170 --> 00:29:50.170
We'd need a substantial loan.

449
00:29:50.250 --> 00:29:53.000
You don't own all 18 of those properties
outright. do you?

450
00:29:55.000 --> 00:29:59.130
I got a banker in San Francisco
I've done business with for years.

451
00:30:00.840 --> 00:30:01.840
Drink?

452
00:30:01.920 --> 00:30:03.250
No. thank you. I don't drink.

453
00:30:09.130 --> 00:30:14.670
You know there's not a single black-owned
building in downtown Los Angeles.

454
00:30:14.750 --> 00:30:16.250
There's a reason for that.

455
00:30:16.340 --> 00:30:18.630
Yeah. We're probably gonna
have to overpay to get it.

456
00:30:20.170 --> 00:30:21.550
Tell me something I don't know.

457
00:30:23.090 --> 00:30:24.090
Now...

458
00:30:25.590 --> 00:30:26.630
convince me.

459
00:30:29.090 --> 00:30:30.090
Well...

460
00:30:31.920 --> 00:30:34.840
the best place to learn about the present
state of the real estate market

461
00:30:34.920 --> 00:30:36.340
is inside of a bank.

462
00:30:36.420 --> 00:30:39.130
We get that building.
we'll be inside 12 of them.

463
00:30:40.000 --> 00:30:43.750
And next time they'll think twice about
refusing to make loans to us

464
00:30:44.340 --> 00:30:45.750
if we're their landlords.

465
00:30:47.880 --> 00:30:50.420
That's very audacious. Mr. Garrett.

466
00:30:51.090 --> 00:30:53.040
I think of it in purely logical terms.

467
00:30:54.380 --> 00:30:55.380
What a shame.

468
00:30:55.790 --> 00:30:56.840
Excuse me?

469
00:30:56.920 --> 00:31:00.000
What about the thrill
of taking it to the man?

470
00:31:00.090 --> 00:31:02.340
In his own castle. no less?

471
00:31:03.670 --> 00:31:04.670
No?

472
00:31:06.790 --> 00:31:07.790
Never mind.

473
00:31:08.840 --> 00:31:13.460
But on purely logical terms.
I have a concern about your plan.

474
00:31:13.540 --> 00:31:14.880
What's that?

475
00:31:15.420 --> 00:31:19.210
All this information we'll be getting
from hanging around all these bankers

476
00:31:19.300 --> 00:31:23.130
is gonna be about
property in white neighborhoods.

477
00:31:27.170 --> 00:31:33.050
Do you plan on starting to buy real estate
in white-only neighborhoods. Mr. Garrett?

478
00:31:33.840 --> 00:31:35.500
That's exactly what we're gonna do.

479
00:31:40.670 --> 00:31:44.790
And just how in the hell
do you plan on pulling that off?

480
00:31:45.630 --> 00:31:47.790
The same way we're gonna buy
the Bankers Building.

481
00:31:54.210 --> 00:31:55.630
You want me to what?

482
00:31:55.710 --> 00:31:58.340
Be us to the rest of the world.

483
00:31:59.540 --> 00:32:03.040
I don't know anything about banking.
I don't know how to buy a bank.

484
00:32:03.130 --> 00:32:04.880
We're not actually buying a bank.

485
00:32:04.960 --> 00:32:07.250
We're buying a building
that the banks are in.

486
00:32:07.750 --> 00:32:08.840
The banks are tenants.

487
00:32:10.670 --> 00:32:11.500
Right.

488
00:32:11.590 --> 00:32:13.420
You'd just be the face of our partnership.

489
00:32:14.540 --> 00:32:16.840
You think I'm.
you know. qualified for this?

490
00:32:16.920 --> 00:32:18.790
We'll teach you everything
you need to know.

491
00:32:22.540 --> 00:32:24.750
That guy? Seriously?

492
00:32:25.250 --> 00:32:26.880
He just has to digest it.

493
00:32:26.960 --> 00:32:27.960
So. what?

494
00:32:28.050 --> 00:32:30.420
He can freeze up
soon as we send him in the room?

495
00:32:30.500 --> 00:32:31.540
He won't freeze up.

496
00:32:31.630 --> 00:32:33.290
Trust me. He's the right guy.

497
00:32:33.380 --> 00:32:37.670
I'll lay you a hundred dollars to your one
he can't go the distance.

498
00:32:38.090 --> 00:32:39.710
Don't you know any other white people

499
00:32:39.790 --> 00:32:41.710
who'd like to get paid
to be our front man?

500
00:32:41.790 --> 00:32:43.380
Not that I trust. Do you?

501
00:32:43.750 --> 00:32:45.170
I don't trust white people.

502
00:32:45.920 --> 00:32:47.630
How do you even go through life like that?

503
00:32:47.710 --> 00:32:49.670
Truth be told.
I don't trust black people either.

504
00:32:50.880 --> 00:32:52.210
What are you even saying?

505
00:32:52.290 --> 00:32:55.170
Look. I do plenty of business
with white folks.

506
00:32:55.250 --> 00:32:56.250
I'm friendly with them.

507
00:32:56.340 --> 00:32:58.090
Good friends with some.

508
00:32:58.170 --> 00:33:01.000
I'm just saying that no matter what.

509
00:33:01.090 --> 00:33:05.050
there's always something extra
going on in the relationship.

510
00:33:05.130 --> 00:33:06.590
It's just the way shit is.

511
00:33:06.670 --> 00:33:08.380
When you accept that.

512
00:33:08.460 --> 00:33:11.750
you can't get caught off guard
when it rears its ugly head.

513
00:33:12.420 --> 00:33:14.040
I can't live my life like that.

514
00:33:14.540 --> 00:33:16.090
See. that's what I like about you.

515
00:33:16.790 --> 00:33:18.340
You are a good person.

516
00:33:18.420 --> 00:33:20.540
