591
00:37:03.960 --> 00:37:04.960
It's him.

592
00:37:05.590 --> 00:37:07.710
You sure you don't wanna give me
that dollar now?

593
00:37:10.170 --> 00:37:11.790
The old way of valuing a building

594
00:37:11.880 --> 00:37:15.210
is the number of years rent it takes
to pay off the price of a building.

595
00:37:15.750 --> 00:37:17.710
So. if the building costs $300.000

596
00:37:17.800 --> 00:37:21.670
and you're getting $30.000 net income
per year. it's a ten multiple.

597
00:37:21.750 --> 00:37:25.340
Today most people value buildings
using the capitalization rate.

598
00:37:25.750 --> 00:37:27.380
But they're mathematically related.

599
00:37:28.210 --> 00:37:31.090
So the cap rate
is the multiplicative inverse

600
00:37:31.170 --> 00:37:33.340
of the ten multiple
we were just talking about.

601
00:37:34.500 --> 00:37:38.090
300.000 = 30.000 x M.

602
00:37:38.170 --> 00:37:42.420
M = ten years.

603
00:37:42.500 --> 00:37:46.670
One-tenth x 300.000 = 30.000.

604
00:37:48.710 --> 00:37:51.840
One-tenth is 10%.

605
00:37:53.090 --> 00:37:54.090
Your cap rate.

606
00:37:58.040 --> 00:38:00.090
Maybe we should start with a math review.

607
00:38:01.290 --> 00:38:02.380
That'd be great.

608
00:38:13.290 --> 00:38:15.210
- Right?
- You have to carry the four.

609
00:38:16.170 --> 00:38:17.170
Which four?

610
00:38:27.170 --> 00:38:30.840
Even on a putt. keep your f-ing head down.

611
00:38:30.920 --> 00:38:32.420
Keep my f-ing head down. Keep...

612
00:38:38.710 --> 00:38:41.500
There's a subtraction error in there
and that last step is wrong.

613
00:38:41.590 --> 00:38:44.840
But other than that
you're getting the gist of it.

614
00:38:47.290 --> 00:38:48.290
Sorry.

615
00:38:48.380 --> 00:38:49.380
Sorry.

616
00:38:49.460 --> 00:38:50.460
Sorry!

617
00:38:57.170 --> 00:38:58.170
Right.

618
00:38:58.250 --> 00:39:00.540
Now multiply by 1.25.

619
00:39:01.290 --> 00:39:02.880
1.25...

620
00:39:04.340 --> 00:39:07.000
No. No. no. no. Stop! Stop!

621
00:39:11.210 --> 00:39:12.420
No. no. no.

622
00:39:13.040 --> 00:39:14.170
Stop laughing.

623
00:39:16.210 --> 00:39:17.670
What the hell?

624
00:39:19.290 --> 00:39:20.420
Hit it.

625
00:39:20.500 --> 00:39:21.590
I am hitting it!

626
00:39:27.550 --> 00:39:29.090
Careful now. Don't hurt yourself.

627
00:39:31.380 --> 00:39:32.550
Stop. Just stop.

628
00:39:35.380 --> 00:39:39.040
We're about 50 yards from the green.
so we're gonna use a wedge.

629
00:39:45.750 --> 00:39:48.960
And you wanna swing it 'bout this hard.

630
00:39:53.630 --> 00:39:56.460
Remember. it's a wedge.
so don't be scared to swing it.

631
00:39:56.550 --> 00:39:57.710
What else you gonna do?

632
00:39:57.800 --> 00:39:59.250
Keep my f-ing head down.

633
00:39:59.340 --> 00:40:00.550
Jesus. Come on.

634
00:40:12.130 --> 00:40:13.130
It's right...

635
00:40:17.460 --> 00:40:19.880
Holy shit. Oh. my...

636
00:40:19.960 --> 00:40:20.960
Come on.

637
00:40:21.800 --> 00:40:23.550
I just kept my f-ing head down and...

638
00:40:31.800 --> 00:40:35.170
It's 432.000.

639
00:40:39.710 --> 00:40:41.420
Yeah. Yeah. that's right.

640
00:40:41.500 --> 00:40:43.180
You got it right. man.
You're getting this.

641
00:41:44.750 --> 00:41:46.000
What you want. Bernard?

642
00:41:46.090 --> 00:41:47.210
This is my time.

643
00:41:48.630 --> 00:41:49.750
I wanna buy a building.

644
00:41:51.630 --> 00:41:56.130
It has a $100.000 annual gross income.
8% vacancy rate.

645
00:41:56.710 --> 00:42:01.710
$12.000 annual operating costs
and I require a 10% cap rate.

646
00:42:03.790 --> 00:42:06.000
What's the maximum purchase amount
I can offer?

647
00:42:12.920 --> 00:42:13.960
Where'd that go?

648
00:42:15.590 --> 00:42:19.170
Straight down the middle. 'bout...

649
00:42:20.420 --> 00:42:23.590
Shit. I don't even know.
I ain't never hit a ball that far.

650
00:42:23.670 --> 00:42:24.840
It's 800.000.

651
00:42:27.920 --> 00:42:29.420
- He's right.
- You're right.

652
00:42:29.500 --> 00:42:30.750
- He's right?
- Yeah.

653
00:42:31.960 --> 00:42:33.750
We have created a monster.

654
00:42:33.840 --> 00:42:35.000
You made the algebra easy.

655
00:42:35.090 --> 00:42:37.340
A month ago. you didn't know
what algebra was. Matt.

656
00:42:37.420 --> 00:42:39.130
- That's true.
- You have a knack for it.

657
00:42:43.880 --> 00:42:44.920
He's ready.

658
00:42:45.670 --> 00:42:47.800
Yep. He's ready.

659
00:42:49.130 --> 00:42:52.420
The Bankers Building is owned
by Charles Renault.

660
00:42:53.380 --> 00:42:55.090
It's 14 stories.

661
00:42:55.170 --> 00:42:58.630
119.000 square feet of commercial space.

662
00:42:59.710 --> 00:43:01.500
It was built in 1929.

663
00:43:01.590 --> 00:43:04.880
And it's still the tallest
commercial building downtown

664
00:43:04.960 --> 00:43:08.290
<i>and generally considered the crown jewel
of downtown architecture.</i>

665
00:43:12.500 --> 00:43:13.880
That's his office?

666
00:43:13.960 --> 00:43:15.340
That's his office.

667
00:43:16.130 --> 00:43:18.040
<i>A converted ballroom.</i>

668
00:43:18.840 --> 00:43:21.090
<i>Holy shit. How rich is this guy?</i>

669
00:43:21.170 --> 00:43:22.250
<i>Very.</i>

670
00:43:22.750 --> 00:43:26.090
<i>Now. he won't take you seriously
without a proper introduction.</i>

671
00:43:26.170 --> 00:43:31.590
But I have arranged for you to bump
into him at the Hancock Park country club.

672
00:43:32.550 --> 00:43:34.880
Wait. that's the most exclusive club
in the city.

673
00:43:34.960 --> 00:43:36.170
I can't just walk in.

674
00:43:36.250 --> 00:43:37.340
Don't worry about that.

675
00:43:53.590 --> 00:43:55.380
Mr. Steiner. welcome.

676
00:43:55.460 --> 00:43:56.460
Thank you.

677
00:43:56.550 --> 00:43:59.420
Arrangements have been made
for you to use our club as a guest.

678
00:43:59.500 --> 00:44:02.340
per our exchange program
with your home club in Pennsylvania.

679
00:44:02.960 --> 00:44:05.300
Will your chauffeur be
waiting on the premises?

680
00:44:07.500 --> 00:44:09.040
I'll be just outside the gate.

681
00:44:09.670 --> 00:44:11.630
Anything goes south. you come find me.

682
00:44:12.460 --> 00:44:14.130
That won't happen. Mr. Morris.

683
00:44:15.880 --> 00:44:17.000
I promise.

684
00:44:17.090 --> 00:44:18.090
Thank you. Anton.

685
00:44:21.880 --> 00:44:23.790
- I'm worried.
- About what?

686
00:44:23.880 --> 00:44:25.920
I don't always do great under pressure.

687
00:44:26.710 --> 00:44:28.290
Come on. You're a natural.

688
00:44:28.380 --> 00:44:30.550
- Natural what?
- Performer.

689
00:44:31.500 --> 00:44:32.590
How do you know that?

690
00:44:32.670 --> 00:44:35.750
You think I got where I am in life
without being able to spot talent?

691
00:44:38.670 --> 00:44:39.670
Go get him.

692
00:44:40.920 --> 00:44:41.960
Yes. sir.

693
00:44:51.300 --> 00:44:52.340
Mr. Steiner?

694
00:44:53.040 --> 00:44:54.040
Yes?

695
00:44:54.130 --> 00:44:56.600
Jackie says you're playing as a single.
looking to be paired up.

696
00:44:56.630 --> 00:44:58.090
Always looking for a good game.

697
00:44:58.840 --> 00:45:00.710
If I can find someone to give me one.

698
00:45:00.790 --> 00:45:02.290
Charles Renault. good to meet you.

699
00:45:04.250 --> 00:45:05.710
Enjoying playing dress-up?

700
00:45:05.790 --> 00:45:07.880
You should try it sometime.
It's thrilling.

701
00:45:08.540 --> 00:45:09.880
No. thanks.

702
00:45:09.960 --> 00:45:13.210
So. you're okay with having a white boy
do your business for you.

703
00:45:13.300 --> 00:45:14.960
but you're not okay putting on a cap

704
00:45:15.040 --> 00:45:17.040
so you can keep an eye on him
while he does it?

705
00:45:17.590 --> 00:45:20.380
It's the only job I've been able to avoid
my entire life.

706
00:45:20.920 --> 00:45:22.590
I'd like to try and keep it that way.

707
00:45:36.540 --> 00:45:38.420
Jimmy. I think we got ourselves a game.

708
00:45:40.170 --> 00:45:41.210
Okay.

709
00:45:41.960 --> 00:45:43.500
So. we're really gonna do this now?

710
00:45:43.590 --> 00:45:47.130
If by "we." you mean "you." yeah.

711
00:46:09.130 --> 00:46:10.170
Remember.

712
00:46:11.130 --> 00:46:12.250
eyes on the ball.

713
00:46:12.340 --> 00:46:13.590
And keep my f-ing head down.

714
00:46:17.880 --> 00:46:19.000
Make me proud. son.

715
00:46:28.250 --> 00:46:31.000
He's gonna claim he's renting
for 20 cents a square foot.

716
00:46:31.090 --> 00:46:32.090
but that's poppycock.

717
00:46:32.170 --> 00:46:33.170
It's more like 15.

718
00:46:35.540 --> 00:46:39.840
<i>See. this whole thing is about getting you
to agree to a higher base value.</i>

719
00:46:39.920 --> 00:46:41.460
Which I won't do.

720
00:46:41.540 --> 00:46:43.880
He's gonna test you. Probe you.

721
00:46:52.500 --> 00:46:56.590
You give him the slightest reason
to doubt your command of the numbers.

722
00:46:56.670 --> 00:46:58.500
he'll see straight through you.

723
00:46:58.590 --> 00:46:59.710
So you gotta impress him.

724
00:47:00.750 --> 00:47:02.090
<i>Like you did on the first tee.</i>

725
00:47:03.130 --> 00:47:04.130
Okay. so what do I do?

726
00:47:04.210 --> 00:47:07.670
What's the equivalent
of a 300-yard tee shot in negotiation?

727
00:47:09.920 --> 00:47:11.130
A four-course lunch.

728
00:47:19.540 --> 00:47:21.290
Flown in from France once a week.

729
00:47:22.380 --> 00:47:23.380
Enjoy.

730
00:47:29.000 --> 00:47:31.340
Okay. we lease at 20 cents a square foot.

731
00:47:31.420 --> 00:47:34.630
That's 272.880 gross per year.

732
00:47:34.710 --> 00:47:36.290
Eighty thousand expenses.

733
00:47:36.380 --> 00:47:38.250
That's 192.880 in profit.

734
00:47:38.920 --> 00:47:43.040
10% cap rate on that
will get us to 1.928.880.

735
00:47:43.540 --> 00:47:47.960
25% premium on that would be 2.411.100.

736
00:47:49.540 --> 00:47:51.880
If that's what you're offering.
I'm interested.

737
00:47:55.130 --> 00:47:56.340
Here's my problem. Charles.

738
00:47:56.420 --> 00:47:58.960
I know you have leases
at 15 cents a square foot.

739
00:47:59.050 --> 00:48:00.500
You know. big long-term leases.

740
00:48:00.590 --> 00:48:02.520
So even if you have
a few suckers paying 20 cents...

741
00:48:02.540 --> 00:48:03.630
More than a few.

742
00:48:04.920 --> 00:48:06.540
Fine. call the average 18 cents.

743
00:48:06.630 --> 00:48:08.380
so that would be a net income of...

744
00:48:08.460 --> 00:48:12.000
245.592. But that's not important.

745
00:48:12.090 --> 00:48:14.960
I mean. if you wanna show me your leases
and prove it. okay.

746
00:48:15.050 --> 00:48:17.130
Otherwise. I'd call it
15 cents a square foot.

747
00:48:17.210 --> 00:48:19.000
- Fifteen is too low.
- Fifteen is generous.

748
00:48:19.090 --> 00:48:21.880
Especially when you factor in vacancies.
which are at least 9%.

749
